Some things are not yet finished in this code.

1. Pass arguments to functions using the parameter struct,
   without unpacking it.

2. Reduce use of calculate-potential-at-all-points routines,
   to improve loop fusion possibilities.

3. (linked to 2) reduce number of unnecessary workspace temporary fields,
   and do we really need Q?

4. Find a way to tidy fields, perhaps into a single struct.

5. (best done after 2 and 3) add openmp pragmas to improve performance on
   desktops when tweaking parameters lots, without adding proper domain	
   decomposition and halo routines. Or maybe use UPC?

6. (linked to 1 and 3) standardise order of arguments to functions